${\mathrm{GFR = 141 \times min}}{\left({{{\mathrm{S}}_{{\mathrm{Cr}}}}{\mathrm{/\kappa , 1}}} \right)^{\mathrm{\alpha }}}{\mathrm{ \times max}}{\left({{{\mathrm{S}}_{{\mathrm{Cr}}}}{\mathrm{/\kappa , 1}}} \right)^{{\mathrm{ - 1}}{\mathrm{.209}}}}{\mathrm{ \times 0}}{\mathrm{.99}}{{\mathrm{3}}^{{\mathrm{Age}}}}{\mathrm{ \times 1}}{\mathrm{.018 }}\left[{{\mathrm{if\ female}}} \right]{\mathrm{ \times 1}}{\mathrm{.159 }}\left[{{\mathrm{if\ black}}} \right]$\end{document}, where SCr is the standardized serum creatinine in mg/dL, κ is 0.7 for females and 0.9 for males, a is −0.329 for females and −0.411 for males, min indicates the minimum of SCr /κ or 1, and max indicates the maximum of SCr /κ or 1. In this study, eGFR values were presented in mL/min/1.73 m2.
